{"title":"New Allied ALFA Balances Ride Quality w/ Some Serious Alpha Vibes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-allied-alfa-balances-ride-quality-w-some-serious-alpha-vibes/","date":1690922398000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"2023 allied alfa road bike shown with rider aboard\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1.jpg 2100w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Aiming to kill your (pavement) quiver with a balanced blend of comfort, stiffness, aerodynamics, and ride quality, the newest iteration of the Allied ALFA road bike says it hits all the right notes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Quick background: The ALFA was <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/hia-velo-launches-allied-cycle-works-premium-usa-made-alfa-road-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Allied’s original model</a>, debuting way back in 2017 with <em>*gasp*</em> rim brakes, making it certainly due for an update. They quickly followed that up with the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/allied-cycle-works-quietly-hits-gravel-new-alfa-road-model/\" target=\"_blank\">Alfa All-Road model</a> with more tire clearance (which was eventually <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-allied-cycle-works-echo-transforms-from-race-ready-road-frame-to-gravel-grinder/\" target=\"_blank\">rebadged as the Echo</a>), and both bikes quickly got disc brakes that year. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1620\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of 2023 allied alfa road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4.jpg 1620w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4-297x220.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4-800x593.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4-120x89.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4-768x569.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-4-1536x1138.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new ALFA frame is a bit stiffer than before, using their “steering spine” layup and design of the fork, and they focused a lot of improving front end lateral stiffness. That comes from a different layup schedule, and also refined shaping and switched to a Mitsubishi MR60 carbon fiber, which they say is super expensive but has the best stiffness-to-weight ratio and is made in the USA and certified for aerospace use.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They call the handling “reactive, but not twitchy; fluid, but not sloppy.” It’s designed to be a race bike that can be ridden every day, for climbing, descending, and all things in between.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Those new shapes keep low-profile (smaller diameter) tubes, but give them a truncated NACA profile. They say the smaller diameter provides a smoother ride quality, and the shapes add “real world aerodynamics” in a variety of crosswind angles your likely to encounter on normal rides.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7.jpg\"><img width=\"1400\" height=\"1753\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7.jpg\" alt=\"closeup view of stem and headset on 2023 allied alfa road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7-240x300.jpg 240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7-800x1002.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7-96x120.jpg 96w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7-768x962.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-7-1227x1536.jpg 1227w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Unlike pretty much every other road bike that’s gone to an integrated internal routing system by using the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-aeroset-brings-full-internal-cable-integration-to-classic-headsets/\">Chris King Aeroset 3 headset</a> (which runs the cables alongside the steerer tube), Allied feeds the brake lines through the stem and directly into the fork’s steerer, allowing them to use a smaller head tube profile and Chris King’s standard Dropset headset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This requires use of their proprietary stem, but it means there’s no cables running through a hole in the upper headset cup, so it should do better at keeping moisture and muck out of your frame. They’ve been using this system on the Echo for a couple of years.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"rear angle view of 2023 allied alfa road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It also means there’s not really room for shift cables, so the bike is only compatible with electronic drivetrains. But it does keep a simple, classic threaded bottom bracket. Framesets include their stem, and their seatpost, which they make themselves, in house, including the hardware.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6.jpg\"><img width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6.jpg\" alt=\"rear angle view of 2023 allied alfa road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6.jpg 2100w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-6-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tire clearance increases to for 32mm tires, and all complete bikes come set up tubeless with Orange Seal sealant inside.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a 0:22 silent video showing it off:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5.jpg\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1366\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5.jpg\" alt=\"side view of 2023 allied alfa road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/2023-allied-alfa-road-bike-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Framesets run $5,500, and complete bikes start at $8,225 and run over $14,000 before you start adding custom paint. It comes in six sizes (48 thru 61) and has a claimed frame weight of 820g (size 56) with a 320g fork.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://alliedcycleworks.com/collections/alfa\" target=\"_blank\">AlliedCycleWorks.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-allied-alfa-balances-ride-quality-w-some-serious-alpha-vibes/\">New Allied ALFA Balances Ride Quality w/ Some Serious Alpha Vibes</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a1fde35d934dec73872ae82deea95824669cc3cce69ffe1a9b6f0a2cfa896d6b","category":"Cycling"}